node.text: You and your partner should be each other’s biggest supports - but not each other’s biggest enablers. Your partner should know what your goal is and help you see it through. When you’re low or frustrated your partner should be there to remind you of who you’re trying to become and that you can absolutely make it. But you have to welcome empathy over sympathy. You have to give them permission to help keep you focused and motivated. It doesn’t help for them to get angry or sad with you. It helps to be understood, absolutely, but when you fall, you don’t need someone to get on the floor with you, you need someone that can help you back up. If you want to learn more about this idea and many others, be sure to join @lisabilyeu and I for our YouTube show Relationship Theory. Link in bio.

node.title: When Your Partner Needs A Kick In The Ass

node.text: You and your partner should be each other’s biggest supports - but not each other’s biggest enablers. Your partner should know what your goal is and help you see it through. When you’re low or frustrated your partner should be there to remind you of who you’re trying to become and that you can absolutely make it. But you have to welcome empathy over sympathy. You have to give them permission to help keep you focused and motivated. It doesn’t help for them to get angry or sad with you. It helps to be understood, absolutely, but when you fall, you don’t need someone to get on the floor with you, you need someone that can help you back up. If you want to learn more about this idea and many others, be sure to join @lisabilyeu and I for our YouTube show Relationship Theory. Link in bio.

node.text:
I have been thinking a lot about decision-making. In fact some of you may have already participated in my Business Decision-Making Workshop. What this work has revealed to me is that much of my success has hinged on my ability to learn from mistakes and develop a system earned from those mistakes to make better decisions.

You cannot be a passive observer in your life (be it business, relationship, etc.). By adopting that mindset you will let the world happen to you. Your mistakes will be seen as punishments the world has set upon you. You must instead claim authority over your life and run headfirst into living. Make mistakes. Learn. Keep running forward. This is the only way I have discovered to get the life you want.

🖊 @paulocoelho
